through a universe of thorns 
having no feathers but smooth 
skin and wingflaps of nearly 
transparent lugubrious membrane there's lightning 
by firing of eyes thunder 
by flapping of wings cowboys 
leaving a trail of moonshine 
fire at the heart of 
it while the legend disappears 
rumors persist of a big 
dead bird nailed to a 
barn with a mighty span 
unfurled and several men posed 
